  "text": "Fluorescence lifetimes characterize the average time that a molecule remains in the excited state prior to returning to the ground state [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] . Lifetimes can be measured either in the time domain, where the time-dependent fluorescence excited by a very short pulse of light is analyzed, or in the frequency domain, where fluorescence is examined during excitation with a repetitive modulation of the light intensity with harmonic components. We use the latter method with a single modulation frequency to achieve rapid data acquisition.",
